				\begin{document}$$Ij{\mathrm{ = }}Ij{\mathrm{wt/}}\left| {\mathrm{N}} \right| - Ij{\mathrm{ki/}}\left| {\mathrm{M}} \right|$$\end{document}Ij=Ijwt∕N-Ijki∕MWhere A
ij is the Hellinger-transformed abundance of OTU i in sample j. N is a subset of all wide-type enriched OTUs in these key OTUs. M is a subset of all mutation-enriched OTUs in these key OTUs. And |N| and |M| are the sizes of these two sets. By using the “pROC” package of R software, we then computed the 95% CI of the AUC with 1000 bootstrap replicates to assess the variability of the measure.
